================================================================================
Bulk Password Generation Benchmarks
================================================================================

Current generateMultiple Performance (Sequential)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
generateMultiple (count=1)                       0.082 ms/op     12130 ops/s  1.1 MB
generateMultiple (count=10)                      0.219 ms/op      4569 ops/s  833.0 KB

generateMultiple (count=100)                     1.920 ms/op       521 ops/s  -1218008 B
generateMultiple (count=500)                    12.108 ms/op        83 ops/s  5.2 MB

Service-level generateMultiplePasswords (Sequential)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
generateMultiplePasswords (count=1)              0.050 ms/op     19966 ops/s  -401608 B
generateMultiplePasswords (count=10)             0.326 ms/op      3071 ops/s  -2777672 B
generateMultiplePasswords (count=50)             0.826 ms/op      1210 ops/s  2.8 MB
generateMultiplePasswords (count=100)            1.882 ms/op       531 ops/s  -623616 B

Single vs Multiple Generation Comparison
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Single generation x 10                           0.186 ms/op      5384 ops/s  3.1 MB
Bulk generation (count=10)                       0.142 ms/op      7023 ops/s  -915896 B

Port Initialization Overhead
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Service recreation x 10                          0.245 ms/op      4075 ops/s  -676920 B

================================================================================
Performance Analysis
================================================================================
Bulk vs Sequential Efficiency: 23.3% improvement
Total Memory Delta: 19.9 MB

Bottleneck Analysis:
1. Sequential generation in generateMultiple method
2. Individual randomGenerator.generateRandomInt calls per character
3. Repeated validation overhead per password
4. No batched random number generation
